The vilicus· was the head slave on a farm, whose duty it was to look after the proper discharge of all farm works: Cato de Re Rust. 142 vilici officia quae sunt, quae dominus praecepit, ea omnia quae in fundo fieri oportet, quaeque emi pararique oportet. eadem uti curet faciatque moneo, dominique dicto audiens sit. mihi me reddentis, ‘that makes me my own master again‚’ i. e. where I can live as I please, without being distracted by the endless claims made upon me at Rome.
